<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870119-0114 </DOCNO><HL> Bob Evans Buys Sausage Firm</HL><DD> 01/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BOBETENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> COLUMBUS, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bob Evans Farms Inc. said it completed the acquisition of closely held Owens Country Sausage Inc. for 825,000 Bob Evans common shares.    Based on Bob Evans's closing price of $20.75, up 12.5 cents, in national over-the-counter trading Friday, the acquisition of Richardson, Texas-based Owens has an indicated value of $17.1 million. Owens makes and distributes sausage in nine southern states. Bob Evans sells pork sausage in 19 states and the District of Columbia, and operates 165 family-style restaurants in 11 states. </TEXT></DOC>